= Keyboard Keys

Keyboard key notation displays keys in a styled format.

== Basic Keyboard Keys

Press kbd:[Enter] to submit the form.

Use kbd:[Ctrl+C] to copy text.

== Keyboard Key Combinations

Use kbd:[Ctrl+Shift+N] to open a new window.

Press kbd:[Alt+F4] to close the application.

== Common Keyboard Shortcuts

* kbd:[Ctrl+S] - Save
* kbd:[Ctrl+Z] - Undo
* kbd:[Ctrl+Y] - Redo
* kbd:[Ctrl+F] - Find

== Keyboard Keys with Other Formatting

Press kbd:[Enter] and then *click* the button.

Use kbd:[Ctrl+C] to _copy_ the text.

== Keyboard Keys in Instructions

Step 1: Press kbd:[Ctrl+N] to create a new file.

Step 2: Type your content.

Step 3: Press kbd:[Ctrl+S] to save.

== Keyboard Keys with Links

Learn more keyboard shortcuts at https://example.com[here].

== Multiple Keyboard Keys

Use kbd:[Ctrl+C] to copy and kbd:[Ctrl+V] to paste.

== Special Keys

Press kbd:[Esc] to cancel.

Use kbd:[Tab] to move to the next field.

Press kbd:[Space] to continue.

